    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-19T13:57:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-19T13:57:00-05:00" n="102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                <head>102. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d102fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79-01025A, Box 52, Folder 3. Confidential; Routine; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-19T18:57:00+00:00">February 19, 1954,
                        1857Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>616. Suggest <gloss target="#t_KUGOWN1">KUGOWN</gloss> black diversionary
                    operation: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_DIR1">DIR</gloss> 38984<note n="2" xml:id="d102fn2"
                                >Not found.</note> indicates <persName corresp="#p_MMA1"
                                >Martinez</persName> going Czechoslovakia.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Miami Herald</hi> 19 Feb reprints <hi rend="italic">La
                                Prensa</hi> 18 Feb Mexico U.P. stating <gloss target="#t_WSBURNT1"
                                >WSBURNT</gloss> getting Soviet arms thru medium Czech Finca owner
                            and that arms to be landed from Soviet submarines.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Suggest HQs arrange with RQM search graphics register for photo Soviet
                            sub (or what could pass for Soviet sub) lying close inshore: photo
                            should be poor lacking detail and credibly taken by amateur with box
                            camera from <gloss target="#t_KMFLUSH1">KMFLUSH</gloss> Pacific
                            coast.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_PVC1">Pivall</persName> would give photo to [<hi
                                rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] suggesting following
                            course: <list>
                                <label>A.</label>
                                <item>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PVC1">Pivall</persName> and one trusted
                                    aid take truckload blackflight arms and cache on Pacific
                                    coast;</item>
                                <label>B.</label>
                                <item>[<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] “discover”
                                    submarine photo and public press;</item>
                                <label>C.</label>
                                <item>[<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] order
                                    investigation coastal areas thus leading to discovery Soviet
                                    arms cache and further press publicity.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <pb facs="0227" n="197" xml:id="pg_197"/>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>After photo in hands [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>]
                            and arms cached, operation could be frozen for utmost use. One use would
                            be to complete operation in advance of enemy strategem to embarrass
                                <gloss target="#t_PBPRIME1">PBPRIME</gloss>. Another use would be to
                            complete operation within few hours after enemy propaganda victory.
                            Further value is that once completed, operation would give pretext for
                                [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] possession satellite
                            arms delivered by black-flight.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
